text.section:
In making a determination whether a person should be debarred under § 16-202(b) or § 16-203 of this title, the Board shall conclude whether the integrity of the contracting process and the best interests of the State would be served by debarring the person from entering into contracts with the applicable public bodies. In making its determination, the Board shall consider relevant factors, including:
the nature and seriousness of the act that caused the person to be subject to debarment;
the time the act occurred;
whether and to what extent the person cooperated with authorities in their investigation of the matters;
the conditions under which the person cooperated; and
the conduct of the person since the act occurred.
